Sentencas: Perovskites of different compositions were tested as cathode contact material between an La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 cathode and a Crofer22APU interconnect by resistance measurements at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Comparative study of perovskites as cathode contact materials between an La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 cathode and a Crofer22APU interconnect in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The materials tested were LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 and La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 which are also used as cathodes; La0.8Sr0.2Mn0.5Co0.5O3 and La0.8Sr0.2Mn0.1Co0.3Fe0.6O3, selected for comparing perovskites with different Mn contents; and La0.8Sr0.2Co0.75Fe0.25O3 and La0.8Sr0.2Co0.75Cu0.25O3 for comparing perovskites with high Co content and two possible partial substitutions of the Co.
Titulo: Comparative study of perovskites as cathode contact materials between an La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 cathode and a Crofer22APU interconnect in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The initial area-specific contact resistance (ASR) was found to depend on the electrical conductivity of the measured perovskites.
Titulo: Comparative study of perovskites as cathode contact materials between an La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 cathode and a Crofer22APU interconnect in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Time evolution of the ASR depended on the interactions between the contact material and the interconnect, showing the highest degradation rates for LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3 and La0.8Sr0.2FeO3.
Titulo: Comparative study of perovskites as cathode contact materials between an La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 cathode and a Crofer22APU interconnect in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Chromium from the interconnect reacted with the Sr-containing perovskites forming SrCrO4.
Titulo: Comparative study of perovskites as cathode contact materials between an La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 cathode and a Crofer22APU interconnect in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: With the contact material without strontium chromium-containing perovskites were formed.
Titulo: Comparative study of perovskites as cathode contact materials between an La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 cathode and a Crofer22APU interconnect in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A reduced interfacial reaction was achieved by application of a MnCo1.9Fe0.1O4 spinel protection layer on Crofer22APU in terms resulting in low and stable ASR.
Titulo: Comparative study of perovskites as cathode contact materials between an La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 cathode and a Crofer22APU interconnect in solid oxide fuel cells
